body:
I've got a module where the last port is an input with a default value specified.
When trying to instanciate it using ordered list connection and ignoring the last param it results in error :
`error: Wrong number of ports. Expecting 3, got 2`

However the LRM explicitely allows this (23.3.2.1) this is actually pretty much one of their example of things that should work and where the port should get the default value.


```verilog
module def(
    output logic a,
    input  logic x,
    input  logic y = 1'b1
);  
    assign a = x ^ y;
endmodule


module test(
    output logic a,
    input  logic x
);  
    def def_I ( a, x );
endmodule
```

Testing with `-g2012` flag on `Icarus Verilog version 13.0 (devel) (s20221226-127-gdeeac2ed-dirty)`

